Trend

death vs time by year

plot = 
  read_csv("./data/maindata.csv") %>% 
  separate(date_of_death, c("year", "month", "day")) %>% 
  filter(year != 2021)
## Rows: 30651 Columns: 12
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (7): age_bin, gender, race, city, state, highest_force, intended_force
## dbl  (4): unique_id, age, latitude, longitude
## date (1): date_of_death
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
#setwd("./plot")  

plot %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarize(count = n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = count, group = 1)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Estimated innocent death over time",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Number of innocent death") 

  #transition_reveal(as.integer(year))

#setwd("..")

death vs time by age

plot %>% 
  group_by(year,age_bin) %>% 
  summarize(count = n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = count, color = age_bin, group = age_bin)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Estimated innocent death over time by age group",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Number of innocent death") +
  scale_x_discrete(breaks = seq(2000, 2020, 4))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
